@startuml states-runner-process
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title State machine — ActiveEntry / llama-server runner process

' Tracks an ActiveEntry through its lifecycle in runners/launch.ts.
' Same state machine for chat models AND for the managed embedder —
' the only difference is `launchedBy` and `customArgs`.

[*] --> Requested

state "Requested" as Requested {
  description : launchModelByPath(path, opts)\ncalled by:\n• UI Run button (launchedBy:null)\n• MCP models.run (launchedBy:'via MCP — …')\n• embedderLifecycle (launchedBy:'embedder')
}

Requested --> Validating : args + path OK
Requested --> RejectedEarly : invalid args /\nfile missing /\nread-only location

state "Validating" as Validating {
  description : resolveCanonicalShardPath()\n+ pickRunnerFor(filePath, sidecar)\n+ port selection (free-port scan)\n+ autotune + sidecar override merge
}

Validating --> Spawning : runner resolved\n+ command built
Validating --> RejectedEarly : no runner /\nport unavailable /\nbuild error

state "Spawning" as Spawning {
  description : child_process.spawn(\n  runner.path,\n  buildCommand(params)\n)\n+ append to ActiveEntry[]\n+ start log ring buffer\n\nllama-server always gets\n--timeout 86400 (24 h,\n2026-05-24) so PR #22907\nnever cancels a long chat.\ncustomArgs override allowed.
}

Spawning --> Booting : pid received
Spawning --> CrashedEarly : ENOENT / EACCES /\nspawn error

state "Booting" as Booting {
  description : Process alive. Stdout/stderr\nstreaming into ring buffer\n(maybe surfaced live to UI).\nlistRunning() shows it but the\nweb UI isn't reachable yet.
}

Booting --> Live : (impl. by polling)\nport answers
Booting --> CrashedEarly : exited within\nfew seconds\n→ auto-open log dialog\n(4.0.15, future)

state "Live" as Live #FFFDF6 {
  description : llama-server responding.\nBrowser URL opened automatically\nfor chat. Routing/embedder callers\nproceed with API calls.
}

Live --> Live : models.list_running\n(snapshot read)
Live --> Stopping : stopProcess(pid)\nOR app quit\nOR models.stop MCP call

state "Stopping" as Stopping {
  description : SIGTERM then SIGKILL\nafter grace. ActiveEntry stays\nin the list with exited=true\nuntil cleared by user / restart.
}

Stopping --> Exited

state "Exited" as Exited {
  description : Process gone. Ring buffer\nstill viewable for debug.\nRemovable from RunningModelsPanel\nvia "Clear exited" action.
}

Exited --> [*] : cleared
RejectedEarly --> [*]
CrashedEarly --> Exited

note bottom of Live
  Three distinct callers reach this
  same state with the same shape:
  Direct (User), via MCP — Claude
  Code (provenance), embedder.
end note

@enduml
